8... Bh5 9. Nc3
{ Now this works well, as  9...Nd4?  10.g4  is great for White. } 9... Qd7
{ Black prepares queenside castling, a logical move.   They can't play  9...Nd4?  due to  10.g4  Nxf3+  @@StartBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/ppp3pp/3p1n2/4p2b/2BnP1P1/2N2N1P/PPP2P2/R1BQ1RK1 b kq g3 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10...Nxg4  11.Nxd4  wins for White@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/ppp3pp/3p1n2/4p2b/2B1P1P1/2N2n1P/PPP2P2/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Qxf3  Bg6  12.g5  Nh5  13.Be6  , which is terrible for Black. }
10. Nd5
{ We have to be precise in this whole line. This move is powerful, as it prevents the move ...Nd4 by tactical means.   Black now can't play  10...Nd4?  , as  12.Nxf6+  gxf6  13.Nxe5!  wins!   Black also can't play the greedy  10...Nxe4??  due to the crushing  11.Re1  Nf6  12.Nxe5!  - very nice! }
