6... Qe7
{ A rare move on the master level, but it is played very frequently below that. It is a welcome sight for us, as the queen move is an early commitment that reaps no benefit for Black. They will most likely reach a worse version of the  6...O-O  lines. }
7. Nc4
{ Piling up on e5, and Black must react to the threat. Now the best move is  7...Nd7  , but we'll also quickly check  7...Bd6  , which is worse. Not as bad as  7...Bg4?  , though - we play  8.Ncxe5  and win the pawn. }
7... Bd6
{ A passive retreat. Black should play  7...Nd7  to start improving the knight. This knight tour is more or less unavoidable; better get it started as soon as possible. }
8. O-O Bg4
{ A tempting move, but Black's pieces are too poorly set up to make it work. }
9. h3 Bh5
{ We insert h3 to push the bishop back and make the next move more effective. }
10. Ne3
{ A clear drawback of Black's formation. The square f5 is weak. If Black plays  10...Bg6  now,  11.Nh4  is strong. }
10... Bg6 11. Nh4 { And we get to f5, which is very annoying for Black. } *

