10... Qe8 { Black prepares ...d6 with this slightly artificial move. } 11. c3
{ We want to prepare d3-d4, of course. At this particular point, there are some interesting alternatives, like  11.Be3  ,  but playing along a central strategy is a logical choice. We are slightly better here, as we manage to play d4 and have more options, like a4, to open the a-file. }
