{ Ouch! Black can't take on d5, so they either have to allow Nxe6 or retreat. }
12... Bd7 13. h4
{ We didn't castle for a reason! Our simple idea is Nxf6+, followed by Qh5 and Black resigns. White is already winning here - amazing! }
13... Nxd5
{ Relatively best for Black, as it gives us a chance to go wrong. After  13...h6  , we'd play  14.Nxf6+  Bxf6  15.Qh5!  , which is similar to the line we are about to check. }
14. Bxd5
{ A crucial move. Worse is  14.exd5?  Bxg5  15.hxg5  Ne7  16.Qh5  Bf5  and Black survives. After the correct bishop recapture, our attack crashes through. }
14... h6 15. Qh5
{ By now, Black already regrets some of their choices, I guess. Black can't take our knight, and we threaten Qg6-h7 mate!   The early knight jump @@StartFEN@@1rbqk2r/2p1bppp/2np1n2/1p2p3/4P3/1BNP1N2/1PP2PPP/R1BQK2R w KQk - 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10.Nd5  is a great option, as we pose some unexpected problems without taking any risks. }
