8... O-O
{ Black avoids the move ...Nc6 and castles. This line became more popular after the strength of @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp1bppp/8/3p4/3Pn3/3B1N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 3 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Nc6  8.Nbd2!  was fully understood. The knight is misplaced in these lines, a defect that delaying ...Nc6 aims to address. Our plan, based on  @@StartFEN@@rn1q1rk1/ppp1bppp/8/3p1b2/3Pn3/3B1N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQR1K1 w - - 6 9@@EndFEN@@  9.Nbd2  ,  still works well. Let's have a look. }
