10... Nxf5 11. Nf1
{ Our plans are simple but effective.   - Play Qd3 next, pushing the knight back to d6.   - Develop the bishop f4.   - Double on the e-file and/or start a kingside initiative based on h4. This depends on Black's setup. }
11... c6
{ Black wants to play this move at some point, getting more stability for the d-pawn.   They also have tried starting with  11...Nd7  , but  12.Qd3  Nd6  13.Bf4  Nf6  14.Re2  remains very nice for White. We double on the e-file, and Black's knight is awkwardly placed. }
12. Qd3 Nd6
{ Black wants to avoid weaknesses caused by ...g6 and rather retreats the knight. }
