13. e6 { Finally, we play this advance. } 13... fxe6 14. Nxd4
{ We'll continue this trainable for a moment, as the rest is forced. } 14...
Nc7 15. Nxe6 Nxe6 16. Qxe6+ Kh8 17. Qe2
{ The simplest move is getting the queen to a safe square. We want to play our knight to e4, but the immediate  17.Ne4  Ne5  leaves our queen in a somewhat strange spot. Black might have ...Bc8 or ...Qc8, when our majesty is not well-placed.  After the retreat, we are ready to play Ne4 to target Black's weakened kingside. They have active pieces, which should give Black about equal chances. I would still rather be White, as Black's king position makes it harder to play. }
