{ We have gained the bishop pair but lost some influence over the center. It will take a moment to finally get our d-pawn to d4, as we will see.  Black now has two basic options: developing with ...e6 or ...g6. Our concept will be similar in both cases. We must play our pawn to d3, retreat our queen to d1, develop the bishop to e3, and then play Nb1-d2-f3. This setup optimally supports the central pawn push d4. }
