{ This is somewhat questionable as now there is no knight on d7 that can recapture on c5 comfortably. }
8. O-O Nc6
{ Or  8...Be7  9.dxc5  Bxc5  10.Re1+  Ne4  11.Be3  , when we manage to trade some minor pieces and reach a favourable position against the IQP. }
9. Re1+ Ne4
{ Not a happy move, but  9...Be7  10.dxc5  O-O  11.b4  just nets a pawn for us. }
10. Bg5
{ White is much better here with many moves. In the first edition, I suggested  10.Bf4  here, while @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/pp1q1ppp/2n5/2pp4/3Pn3/2P2N2/PP3PPP/RNBQR1K1 w kq - 4 10@@EndFEN@@  10.Nbd2  f5  11.Nf1  also looks promising.  After @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/pp1q1ppp/2n5/2pp4/3Pn3/2P2N2/PP3PPP/RNBQR1K1 w kq - 4 10@@EndFEN@@  10.Bg5  Black is in trouble, as they probably have to play the awkward move  10...f6  , creating more weaknesses. After  11.Be3  Black's position is tough to defend. }
