{ We don't need to cover the pawn, a difficult move to play if you don't know the idea. I'll now check  13...Nxc4  as the main move, even though this is not the best reply. Knowing to punish the pawn grab is the most important point, though. }
13... Nxc4
{ This leads to many difficult moments for Black, but we need to check it, of course. What are the alternatives?   A.  13...Be5  14.Nb5!  is a typical idea that you frequently see in this line.   B.  13...Bd7  14.Rd1  Bc5  15.Bf4!  is another idea that occurs often. Always check those counterattacking moves, like Nb5 in A or Bf4 here.   C.  13...Rd8  is probably best when we play  14.Qh4  and Black can't go  14...Nxc4??  due to  15.Nb5  , when the queen is overloaded. Better is @@StartFEN@@r1br2k1/ppq2ppp/1n1bp3/8/2P4Q/2N3P1/PP3PBP/R1B2RK1 b - - 4 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Bd7  , when  15.b3  is slightly better for White, as Black's knight is misplaced. }
