10... O-O
{ Black castles and allows our perfect piece setup! The same type of mistake is  10...f6?!  , when  11.Bd3  is also possible. This move will usually lead to the same positions as @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/1p1nbppp/1qn1p3/p1ppP3/3P1P1P/PPP2N2/6P1/R1BQKBNR b KQkq h3 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10...O-O  , as after  10...f6  11.Bd3  Black will likely castle soon. We'll see that  11...O-O?  fails spectacularly, but  11...cxd4  12.cxd4  O-O  13.Ne2  would work and is 'only' clearly worse for Black. }
11. Bd3
{ Exactly! Now they can't grab the d-pawn, as  11...cxd4  12.cxd4  Nxd4??  13.Nxd4  Qxd4  14.Bxh7+  wins the queen. Black also needs to worry about a possible greek gift sacrifice. We'll check now:   A.  11...f6?  , which allows the greek gift and leads to spectacular lines.   B.  11...cxd4  is better when we can't take on h7, but  12.cxd4  still gives us a huge advantage. Black can also play the passive move @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/1p1nbppp/1qn1p3/p1ppP3/3P1P1P/PPPB1N2/6P1/R1BQK1NR b KQ - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11...f5  12.h5  ,  when we reach a similar position to 10...f5 11. h5, which we have examined already. }
11... f6
{ Falling right into the Greek gift! As mentioned, Black needs to shut down the kingside with 11...f5 or insert the capture on d4. }
12. Bxh7+ { Boom! } 12... Kxh7 13. Ng5+
{ Now, there are some rather easy wins, but Black has one tough defence. }
13... Kh6
{ That's by far the best try.   A.  13...fxg5  14.Qh5+  Kg8  15.hxg5  wins. Black can't stop g6 and Qh8 without sacrificing the house.   B.  13...Kg8  14.Qh5  fxg5  15.hxg5  is a different route to the same position.   C.  13...Kg6  14.h5+  Kh6  15.Qd3  f5  16.Qg3  also crashes through. }
14. Ne2
{ A final, precise move. The idea is Ng3 and Qh5 mate. Black is completely lost now.   A.  14...cxd4  15.Ng3!  g6  16.h5!  shows the basic idea.   B.  14...fxg5  15.hxg5+  Kg6  16.f5+!  Kf7  17.Nf4  Ke8  18.Qh5+  Rf7  19.fxe6  wins the house again.   C.  14...fxg5  15.hxg5+  Kg6  16.f5+!  Rxf5  17.Nf4+  Rxf4  18.Qh5+  Kf5  19.Qh7+  g6  20.Qh3+  Rg4  21.Qf3+  Rf4  22.Qxf4#  even leads to mate. }
