{ This position may also occur via different move orders. Black can start with a much earlier ...Qc7 and then proceed with kingside castling. }
10. Ne5
{ I was surprised to see how effective this move is. The idea is to play Bf4 next, which puts Black's queen in an awkward spot. The two moves to consider are  10...Nxe5  and  10...Bf5  now. }
10... Nxe5
{ A simple solution for Black, but it leads to a very comfortable position for us. }
11. Rxe5
{ It took me a moment to appreciate that Black's task is quite difficult in this position. The combo of Bd3 and Re5 stops ...Bf5, the move Black probably should have played long ago. Now it's going to be hard to accomplish. }
11... Be6
{ Not a great square for the bishop, but nothing is convincing for Black. The engine wants to play  11...e6  and slowly prepare ...e5 by going ...Nd7, still giving White a definite edge. We should retreat our rook to e1 and go for Nd2-f3 next, playing for a kingside attack. Black can go for ...e5, the comp plan, but then would grovel for a draw in an IQP formation. }
12. Nd2
{ We would also have an advantage after a rook retreat, but we can ignore Black's ...Ne4 idea and set a nice trap. }
12... Ne4
{ A tempting move and not a mistake, but on the next move, Black has to play well. }
13. Rxe6
{ The rook had no squares, we need to sacrifice the exchange. Well, you could argue that we are not REALLY giving up the exchange because Black is in terrible shape if they take the rook now. }
13... fxe6
{ A huge mistake. They have to play  13...Nxd2!  , when  14.Re1  Nc4  15.Qf3  is nice for White, but still a playable position for Black. }
14. Nxe4 dxe4 15. Bxe4
{ We have a pawn and a fantastic position for the exchange. Black's e-pawns and the kingside are weak, and the e4-bishop dominates. We'll continue with Be3 and Qe2 to complete development and then see how to convert. You can play for the kingside attack @@StartBracket@@h4-h5 later@@EndBracket@@ or put pressure on the queenside. If Black plays ...e5 at some point, d4-d5 is a good reply. Black's g7-bishop is dead, pretty much. }
