12. Nxe4 Bxe4 13. Nd2 { We get the knight to the queenside with tempo. } 13...
Bf5 14. Nb3
{ The knight is well-placed on b3 in this situation. We want to play Bf4, a4-a5 and jump to c5 later. It is amazing to see how ineffective Black's pieces are. Our opponent has no active idea, which makes it very tough to play. }
