1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8
{ Black retreats the queen on the safest square - on d8, it is certainly not getting into trouble soon. Still, moving the queen twice in the opening, only to return it to its initial square, can't be ideal.How do we play against 3...Qd8 then? The first step is easy. }
